["Like   Jane   and   Joan  , a medieval variant of Old French <i>Je(h)anne</i>. Towards the end of the Middle Ages this form became largely confined to Scotland. In the 20th century it became more widely used in the English-speaking world and enjoyed a period of great popularity, but it is now out of fashion. Among numerous well-known and influential bearers are the British novelists  Jean Plaidy  (  Eleanor Hibbert ,  1910–93 ) and  Jean Rhys  (  Ella Gwendolen Rees Williams ,  1894–1979 ), British actress  Jean Simmons  (  1929–2010 ), and American-born actress  Jean Seberg  (  1938–79 ). It is also found as a variant spelling of the masculine name   Gene ."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["New Testament: ‘God is gracious’.  See  <b>John</b> ."]},{"name":"Jeane","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Jean ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Jean I de Thourotte was born in 1135, in Thourotte, Oise, Picardie, France, his father, Guy DE COUCY, was 26 and his mother, Jeanne de Thourotte, was 16. He had at least 1 son and 2 daughters with Alix de Dreux. He died in 1177, at the age of 42."},"et":{"1135–1177":"1135–1177","1144–1192":"1144–1192","1152–1214":"1152–1214","1156–1210":"1156–1210","1173–1237":"1173–1237","1174–1219":"1174–1219","1181–1237":"1181–1237","1172–1175":"1172–1175","1110–1170":"1110–1170","1119–1163":"1119–1163","1110":"1110","1175":"1175","1163":"1163","1174":"1174","1152":"1152","1173":"1173","1172":"1172","1170":"1170","1181":"1181","1192":"1192","1237":"1237","1214":"1214","1135":"1135","1134":"1134","1156":"1156","1177":"1177","1210":"1210","1144":"1144","1219":"1219","1119":"1119","Thourotte, Oise, Hauts-de-France, France":"Thourotte, Oise, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Coucy-le-Chateau-Auffrique, Aisne, Picardie, France":"Coucy-le-Château-Auffrique, Aisne, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Thourotte, Oise, Picardie, France":"Thourotte, Oise, Picardie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1135–1177":"1135–1177","1144–1192":"1144–1192","1152–1214":"1152–1214","1156–1210":"